ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The course provides a rich approach to the most important readings and issues on the field. It is a must to take for everyone interested in modern Europe. Very useful to plan future graduate research!

A helpful course for anyone with a background in European history of sexuality wanting to do additional research. I would recommend it, although not to someone who had not already worked on the topic.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I have a better knowledge of Freud and Krafft-Ebing, in particular, whom I had read before but never in depth.
